==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: energizing
<hw>en"er*gi`zing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>imparting or capable of imparting vitality and energy.</def>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bracing, brisk, fresh, refreshing, refreshful,
tonic.</syn>
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Those nobler exercises of <qex>energizing</qex> love.</q>
<rj><qau>Bp. Horsley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>supplying motive force.</def> <wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> energizing, energising, kinetic.</syn>
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Energumen</ent>⟦br⟧
